---
Diamond dedup end-to-end: entry → left, right → common AND entry →
common directly. The three importers reach common.fnk via three
different raw relative strings (`./sub/common.fnk`, `./common.fnk`,
`../sub/common.fnk`) which all canonicalise to `./sub/common.fnk`.
common.fnk must be linked exactly once; both left_val and right_val
must see the same `base = 10`, and the program must actually execute.
---
skip-ir test 'diamond with two paths to same dep', fn:
  expect ir_wat ƒink:
    {total} = import './test_link/diamond.fnk'
    total
  | equals wat":
    TODO
